{
  "article_id": "TheYouthsCompanion1880",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "If ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "De Foe",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "dde",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had only known of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a female Crusoe",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "living on ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "an ocean island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", he might, perhaps, have wrought out a story superior to his Robinson Crusoe. Alexander Selkirk's brief life on ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Juan Fernandez",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_jf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was trivial, either in the hardships endured or the difficulties conquered, compared with that of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a native woman",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "on ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "an island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "opposite ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Southern California",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_socal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The Catholic Fathers at South [Santa] Barbara",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were transporting "
      },
      {
        "text": "the natives",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Island St. Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Among them was "
      },
      {
        "text": "a mother",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who discovered that "
      },
      {
        "text": "her babe",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been left behind. She begged that "
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "might be put back, but "
      },
      {
        "text": "the captain",
        "entity_keys": [
          "chu",
          "isp"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "refused. "
      },
      {
        "text": "She leaped into the sea to swim ashore, but, as a storm prevailed, they all thought she was drowned.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Eighteen years after, "
      },
      {
        "text": "a company",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "landed on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". They found traces of life, and after long search discovered "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and took her with them. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The poor mother",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "never found "
      },
      {
        "text": "her babe",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but had managed to live in comparative comfort, though very lonely. "
      },
      {
        "text": "After her long life chiefly in the open air, she could not bear the confinement of a house, and soon sickened and died.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}